    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fælīvyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fælīvyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>fælyvd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fælevun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>fælivd</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>обманывать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>deceive</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>изменять</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>cheat</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>fælyvd</orth></form>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>fælītoj</orth></form>
                        <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                    <q>обманщик</q>
                                </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                    <q>deceiver</q>
                                </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                    <q>плут</q>
                                </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                    <q>cheat</q>
                                </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>afælyvta mæ sawærfyg ræsuǧd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>обманула меня чернобровая красавица</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a black-browed beauty deceived me</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>gædytæ ʒūry, fælītoj!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>врет он, плут!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he is lying, you cheat!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Qazaq"
                            /><biblScope>153</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pati-raip-</w></mentioned>, сращение преверба %ifæ%i (←%ipati-%i) с не
                    сохранившимся самостоятельно глаголом %iliv-%i (из %irip-%i с закономерным
                    перебоем %ir%i → %iI%i перед %ii%i). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>firēftan : firēb-</w>
                        <gloss><q>обманывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>rēw</w>
                        <gloss><q>хитрость</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>коварство</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>frēftan : frēp-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>brēp-</w>
                        <gloss><q>обманывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>βrβʼnt</w>
                        <gloss><q>обман</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>rip-, lip-</w>
                        <gloss><q>мазать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>замазывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>обманывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>rip-</w>
                        <gloss><q>обман</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>ripu-</w>
                        <gloss><q>обманщик</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>плут</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/>
                        <w>lip-</w>
                        <gloss><q>мазать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Исходное значение было ‘мазать’.
                    Поэтому справедливо относят сюда же славянские глаголы со значением ‘лепить’,
                    ‘клеить’ и пр. (<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>лепить, липнуть</w></mentioned>); см. <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope>II 403</biblScope></bibl>. На
                    иранской почве значение ‘мазать’ сохранилось в памирских: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>rofam</w>
                        <gloss><q>я мажу</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Ср. д. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ilivd"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 56, 87, III
                        156</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>20, 34, 61</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pati-raip-</w></mentioned>, a contraction of the preverb %ifæ%i
                    (←%ipati-%i) and a non-retained independently verb %iliv-%i (from %irip-%i with
                    the regular change %ir%i → %iI%i before %ii%i). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>firēftan : firēb-</w>
                        <gloss><q>deceive</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>rēw</w>
                        <gloss><q>slyness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>guile</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>frēftan : frēp-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>brēp-</w>
                        <gloss><q>deceive</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>βrβʼnt</w>
                        <gloss><q>deception</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>rip-, lip-</w>
                        <gloss><q>paint</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>smear</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>deceive</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>rip-</w>
                        <gloss><q>deception</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>ripu-</w>
                        <gloss><q>deceiver</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>cheat</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/>
                        <w>lip-</w>
                        <gloss><q>paint</q></gloss></mentioned>. The initial meaning was ‘smear’.
                    That is why Slavic verb with the meaning ‘mould’, ‘glue’ etc. are also related
                    to it (<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>lepitʼ</w>
                        <gloss><q>stick</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                            ><w>lipnutʼ</w>
                        <gloss><q>be sticky</q></gloss></mentioned>); see <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope>II 403</biblScope></bibl>. In the
                    Iranian languages, the meaning ‘smear’ is retained in Pamir languages:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>rofam</w>
                        <gloss><q>I am smearing</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Cf. Digor <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ilivd"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 56, 87, III
                        156</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>20, 34, 61</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
